The paper deals with neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves manipulating the embeddings of source and target words, which is a common technique in deep learning and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves experimentation with different strategies, which involves optimization and tuning of models, and thus falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of hidden states in the encoding and decoding phases of the translation process also involves the use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs), which is a subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves analysis of the quality of sentence translation and alignment of individual words, which involves the use of computer vision techniques such as attention mechanisms, and thus falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
